==Italian==

===Etymology===
From the Ancient Greek proverb ''γλαυκ̀ εὶς ̀Αθήνας'' (glauk eis Athenas).  See [[bring owls to Athens]].

===Proverb===
'''portare nottole ad Atene'''
# to [[bring owls to Athens]], to [[carry coals to Newcastle]]; to undertake a pointless [[venture]], one that is [[redundant]], [[unnecessary]], [[superfluous]], or highly [[stupid|uneconomical]].